theorem closure_interior_closure_eq_closure_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    closure (interior (closure A)) = closure A := by
  -- `interior (closure A)` is contained in `closure A`,
  -- hence the same holds for their closures.
  have h‚ÇÅ : closure (interior (closure A)) ‚äÜ closure A :=
    closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ‚äÜ closure A)
  -- Because `A` is open and contained in `closure A`,
  -- every point of `A` lies in `interior (closure A)`.
  have hA_sub : (A : Set X) ‚äÜ interior (closure A) := by
    intro x hx
    have h_nhds : (closure A : Set X) ‚àà ùìù x := by
      have hA_nhds : A ‚àà ùìù x := hA.mem_nhds hx
      exact Filter.mem_of_superset hA_nhds subset_closure
    exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 h_nhds
  -- Taking closures of both sides yields `closure A ‚äÜ closure (interior (closure A))`.
  have h‚ÇÇ : closure A ‚äÜ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
    closure_mono hA_sub
  exact Set.Subset.antisymm h‚ÇÅ h‚ÇÇ
